From: mpv-iina-avs <noreply@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] vulkan/gpu_tex: use COLOR_BIT for non-multiplanar MTLTexture import

mpv's VideoToolbox zero-copy interop creates one independent single-plane
VkImage (R16Unorm / RG16Unorm) per CVPixelBuffer plane and imports each
via PL_HANDLE_MTL_TEX with shared_mem.plane = 0. libplacebo then writes
.plane = VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_PLANE_0_BIT into VkImportMetalTextureInfoEXT,
but per the Vulkan spec a non-multiplanar destination VkImage must use
VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_COLOR_BIT. MoltenVK silently drops the import in that
case, leaving the VkImage backed by zeroed memory and producing all-green
output for hwdec=videotoolbox on macOS.

Pick COLOR_BIT for single-plane VkImages and keep PLANE_n_BIT for true
multiplanar destinations.
---
 src/vulkan/gpu_tex.c | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/vulkan/gpu_tex.c b/src/vulkan/gpu_tex.c
index 313f5d77..4d6b8bcd 100644
--- a/src/vulkan/gpu_tex.c
+++ b/src/vulkan/gpu_tex.c
@@ -358,7 +358,16 @@ pl_tex vk_tex_create(pl_gpu gpu, const struct pl_tex_params *params)
 #ifdef VK_EXT_metal_objects
     VkImportMetalTextureInfoEXT import_metal_tex = {
         .sType = VK_STRUCTURE_TYPE_IMPORT_METAL_TEXTURE_INFO_EXT,
-        .plane = VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_PLANE_0_BIT << params->shared_mem.plane,
+        // For multi-planar destination VkImages each plane must be selected
+        // explicitly via VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_PLANE_n_BIT. For single-plane
+        // (non-disjoint) images the spec — and MoltenVK — require
+        // VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_COLOR_BIT; passing PLANE_0_BIT in that case
+        // makes MoltenVK silently skip the import and allocate its own
+        // backing MTLTexture, producing all-green / all-zero samples on
+        // the videotoolbox -> Vulkan zero-copy path.
+        .plane = tex_vk->num_planes
+                     ? (VkImageAspectFlagBits)(VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_PLANE_0_BIT << params->shared_mem.plane)
+                     : VK_IMAGE_ASPECT_COLOR_BIT,
     };
 
     VkImportMetalIOSurfaceInfoEXT import_iosurface = {
-- 
